songs.title: Ramblin’ Man - Live At Jacksonville Veterans Memorial Arena, Jacksonville, FL / May 5, 2017
songs.lyrics:
Lord, I was born a ramblin' man
Tryin' to make a livin' and doin' the best I can
And when it's time for leavin'
I hope you'll understand
That I was born a ramblin' man

My father was a gambler down in Georgia
He wound up on the wrong end of a gun
And I was born in the back seat of a Greyhound bus
Rollin' down highway forty-one

Lord, I was born a ramblin' man
Tryin' to make a livin' and doin' the best I can
And when it's time for leavin'
I hope you'll understand
That I was born a ramblin' man

Yeah I'm on my way to New Orleans this mornin'
I'm movin' out of Nashville, Tennessee
They're always havin' a good time down on the bayou
Lord, them Delta women think the world of me

And Lord, I was born a ramblin' man
Tryin' to make a livin' and doin' the best I can
And when it's time for leavin'
I hope they understand
That I was born a ramblin' man
Lord, I was born a ramblin' man
Lord, I was born a ramblin' man
Lord, I was born a ramblin' man
One more time
Lord, I was born a ramblin' man
Here we go

Yeah Lord, I was born a ramblin' man
And when it's time for leavin'
I hope you understand
That I was born a ramblin' man
